{"TopicId":100181,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Craft-Ception","CreatedByName":"SpenSpaceCorp","CreatedById":98977,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-20T06:21:39Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SpenSpaceCorp","CreatedById":98977,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-20T06:21:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EHello everyone,\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBecause the space program\u0027s budget was recently significantly increased (someone accidentally added an extra digit or two), an attempt at creating a ridiculous \u0022long range\u0022 bomber has resulted in the development of a monstrosity. Instead of overcoming regular boring obstacles, such as \u0022lack of fuel\u0022 and \u0022not enough wings for the too heavy aircraft\u0022, a brilliant Kerbal in the back of the room suggested, \u0022why not just carry another bomber?\u0022 Thus began the idea of craft-ception, putting one craft inside another craft.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBUT WAIT! There\u0027s more! The engineers took this concept to the next level, developing a bomber small enough that could fit withing the Mk. 2 cargo bays, which in turn could be carried inside the Mk. 3 cargo bays!!!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThus, I present to you, \u003Cstrong\u003Ea bomb carrying bomber within a bomber within a bomber\u003C/strong\u003E!!!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe large bomber taking off (rocket assisted):\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/JN8g9XG.png\u0022 alt=\u0022JN8g9XG.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe large bomber releasing the medium bomber:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/h3op5qG.png\u0022 alt=\u0022h3op5qG.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe medium bomber in-flight:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/7wBAZoW.png\u0022 alt=\u00227wBAZoW.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe medium bomber releasing the small bomber:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/YOm754O.png\u0022 alt=\u0022YOm754O.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe small bomber in-flight:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/T7lHa7q.png\u0022 alt=\u0022T7lHa7q.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe small bomber releasing the bomb (the bomb detached too fast for a pic):\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/1KZXj0X.png\u0022 alt=\u00221KZXj0X.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe small bomb in flight:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/y8wo9Rc.png\u0022 alt=\u0022y8wo9Rc.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003EI am curious to see if/what others have done in this regard.\u003C/span\u003E (I think it would be awesome to fit something like this monstrosity within ANOTHER larger cargo bay from a mod!\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-02-20T06:25:08Z\u0022 title=\u002202/20/2015 06:25  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 20, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by SpenSpaceCorp\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Engineer of Stuff","CreatedById":106757,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-20T06:41:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ECool!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pecan","CreatedById":96332,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-20T06:48:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYeah, but that\u0027s not a bomb.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt\u0027s a missile! Which means you have four craft in their, not three plus a dumb payload. Nice!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KSK","CreatedById":61025,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-20T06:54:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pecan\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Pecan\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EYeah, but that\u0027s not a bomb.\u003Cp\u003EIt\u0027s a missile! Which means you have four craft in their, not three plus a dumb payload. Nice!\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESomebody set you up the bomb... \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENice craft though - I liked having two SRBs for a rocket assisted take-off and the lifting body design for Bomber the 2nd was sweet.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sidereus","CreatedById":135263,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-20T07:02:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI kind of have something like this. My orbital Mun Base has a 4-Kerbal lander that shuttles Kerbonauts back and forth from the surface of the Mun. It\u0027s stored in the aft cargo hold when not in use:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v320/Koloblicin/KSP/screenshot103_zpsccb29ftv.png\u0022 alt=\u0022screenshot103_zpsccb29ftv.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELander craft on approach with passenger.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v320/Koloblicin/KSP/screenshot105_zps65v1og4i.png\u0022 alt=\u0022screenshot105_zps65v1og4i.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELander Craft docked inside cargo bay.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v320/Koloblicin/KSP/screenshot106_zps1zbro99p.png\u0022 alt=\u0022screenshot106_zps1zbro99p.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECargo bays closed.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpenSpaceCorp","CreatedById":98977,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-20T07:04:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pecan\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Pecan\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt\u0027s a missile! Which means you have four craft in their, not three plus a dumb payload. Nice!\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E what if I were to attach a missile to that missile?!?!?!?!?!?! \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_ohmy.png\u0022 alt=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E :O \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_ohmy.png\u0022 alt=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#C0C0C0;\u0022\u003E- - - Updated - - -\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERegolith, that is not a bad idea! It would protect the lander from Jeb\u0027s docking/EVA shenanigans.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlso, thank you KSK!\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-02-20T07:06:35Z\u0022 title=\u002202/20/2015 07:06  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 20, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by SpenSpaceCorp\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sidereus","CreatedById":135263,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-20T07:17:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpenSpaceCorp\u0022 data-cite=\u0022SpenSpaceCorp\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERegolith, that is not a bad idea! It would protect the lander from Jeb\u0027s docking/EVA shenanigans.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe lander is remote-controlled, so Jeb doesn\u0027t have much to do when he\u0027s riding in it. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI mainly built it that way because when I got a mission for the orbital mun base, I also had a bunch of Kerbals (including Jeb) stranded on the surface, and having an internally-docked lander minimizes the wonkiness that happens when you try and maneuver the station around vs. having an externally attached ship. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt\u0027s also surprisingly easy to dock. The cargo bay gives a nice reference for lining everything up. I installed the Docking Port Alignment mod specifically to help with this, expecting it to be very difficult, and I hardly even used it. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KSK\u0022 data-cite=\u0022KSK\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003ESomebody set you up the bomb... \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENice craft though - I liked having two SRBs for a rocket assisted take-off and \u003Cstrong\u003Ethe lifting body design for Bomber the 2nd was sweet.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u002B1. It is\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022459\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/_j9QeUoPOi4?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E.\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Yukon0009","CreatedById":109376,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-20T08:17:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E*sees post*\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E*scrambles off to SPH*\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KSK","CreatedById":61025,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-20T11:39:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpenSpaceCorp\u0022 data-cite=\u0022SpenSpaceCorp\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E what if I were to attach a missile to that missile?!?!?!?!?!?! \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_ohmy.png\u0022 alt=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E :O \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_ohmy.png\u0022 alt=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYo dawg...I heard you like missiles?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMan, it\u0027s internet meme day today. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EAlso, thank you KSK!\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYou\u0027re welcome!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Thomas988","CreatedById":92699,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-20T12:45:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWow! That\u0027s awesome! I\u0027ve really lost my touch at building crafts.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rich","CreatedById":17874,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-20T13:00:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpenSpaceCorp\u0022 data-cite=\u0022SpenSpaceCorp\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E what if I were to attach a missile to that missile?!?!?!?!?!?! \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_ohmy.png\u0022 alt=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E :O \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_ohmy.png\u0022 alt=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EReminds me of the missile from Transformers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/WA6Zh7O6DvM?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI have been meaning to build one of these in KSP/Space Engineers.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NecroBones","CreatedById":105424,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-20T14:30:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EBomber nesting-dolls. Nice. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-20T15:02:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ENice, this sort of stuff might be more relevant with the new aero model and reentry heat. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe second image makes me think of the X plane tests, yes I know it was not carried internally.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpacedCowboy","CreatedById":92106,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-20T23:56:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ERussian Dolls\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpenSpaceCorp","CreatedById":98977,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-21T02:28:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpacedCowboy\u0022 data-cite=\u0022SpacedCowboy\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003ERussian Dolls\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOnly high-velocity high-altitude explosives carrying-high thrust Russian dolls XD\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpacedCowboy","CreatedById":92106,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-21T03:03:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpenSpaceCorp\u0022 data-cite=\u0022SpenSpaceCorp\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EOnly high-velocity high-altitude explosives carrying-high thrust Russian dolls XD\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYeah, that too. Excellent craft!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Special Agent Sigvan","CreatedById":92033,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-21T08:34:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAmerica thanks you.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}